Sample.Name: HG-HG0F2
Selection_description (e.g. dermo challe: parent, female. Selectively bred for disease resistance through 12 generations of hatchery mating of small number of breeders (10 – 30 per generation). Gynogenetic diploids were produced in 2013 by blocking the release of polar body II with cytochalasin B in eggs from a single female activated by UV-treated sperm (Guo et al. 1993). NH and HG are all NEH oysters and experienced >12 generations of selection. NH is a core NEH subline, while XGH is an inbred NEH subline. All NEH lines were derived from Long Island Sound. NH and other NEH core sublines received new genetic materials from Long Island Sound. They were maintained by rotational crossing with larger Ne (about 50) to minimize inbreeding. XGH is an inbred line that did not receive new genetic material and had smaller Ne (10-30).
